[1] Saudi Arabia, 4 new cases Jeddah, MOH 7 Apr 2014
Date: Mon 7 Apr 2014
Source: Saudi Arabia Ministry of Health [edited]
http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CoronaNew/PressReleases/Pages/mediastatemenet-2014-04-07-001.aspx


4 cases of novel coronavirus recorded in Jeddah
-----------------------------------------------
Within the framework of the constant monitoring and epidemic surveillance of the novel coronavirus (MERS-CoV), the Ministry of Health (MOH) has announced that 4 cases have been recorded in Jeddah.

The 1st case is a 28 year old male citizen. Now, he is at the IC unit, receiving the proper treatment. The 2nd case is a 35 year old male citizen, who has no symptoms. The 3rd case is 32 year old female citizen, working in the health sector, who also has no symptoms. As for the 4th case, it is a 33 year old male resident, who has no symptoms either.

--
